          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A pulsed-and-bunched deuteron beam at eight energies",
                "between 8.5 and 14.5 MeV. The pulse width was",
                "typically 3 ns (FWHM). Pulse repetition rates of 0.5",
                "and 1 MHz were used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets consisted of 40 microg/cm2 237Np on 200",
                "microg/cm2 Ni backings."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four 600 mm2 surface-barrier fission",
                "detectors (160 microm depletion depth) were placed",
                "symmetrically around the target in the target plane."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " These detectors observed fission fragments",
                "emitted from 237mPu nuclei recoiling out of the",
                "target and decaying either in flight or after being",
                "stopped on the catcher foil. Prompt fission events",
                "occurring in the target were monitored with a 100 mm2,",
                "160 microm depletion-depth surface-barrier fission",
                "detector located at 167.5 degree with respect to the",
                "deuteron beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A large uncertainty must be placed on",
                "these cross sections, since the thickness of the",
                "targets (40 microg/cm2 237Np) precludes a precise",
                "determination of the fraction of 237mPu nuclides",
                "which recoil out of the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
